column1: Unless otherwise agreed, rate increases are effective per the terms of the agreement governing the
relationship of the parties.  Rate decreases are effective on the date indicated above.  The start

The rates contained in this Rate Modification Notice apply to the specific Country-City codes detailed
alongside  such rates.  The Route Descriptions are provided for convenience only.  In all cases  the
country-city codes shall govern. Attached please find a list of all Country-City codes for this rate
If more than twenty percent (20%) of total US Domestic Termination Traffic during any billing
period is terminated in local exchange areas not serviced by a Regional Bell Operating Company
("RBOC") or a wireless operator, an additional charge of $0.03 per minute will be added to traffic in excess of
such twenty percent (20%) threshold.  Any such additional charges, as described in the previous sentence
will be billed as an adjustment to the original invoice for that billing period.
This 80/20 rule excludes calls terminating to Alaska and Hawaii.

By sending traffic to these destinations, Company agrees that it wishes to purchase Premium Services and

Destinations listed as "unchanged" may have been increased on a previously issued rate modification notice
and may have not yet taken effect. Such rates are listed herein as "pending changes".  Unchanged rates on
this rate modification notice DO NOT override pending changes.
If previously increased destinations are restated as unchanged, further increased, or decreased on this
notice and the effective date is greater than the prior effective date, the prior increase date will remain
in effect, with further changes as stated in this notice taking effect on the above listed date.
